Dataset Name: Premier League Matches (2010–2020)


Files Included:
- premier_league_sample.csv : sample version of the dataset
- pic_of_dataset.png        : preview image of the dataset structure


Description:
The Premier League Matches dataset contains detailed statistics for football matches
played between 2010 and 2020. Each record represents a single match and includes
performance metrics for both the home and away teams.

The dataset was obtained from Kaggle and is used in this project for:
- SQL-based data analysis
- Python exploratory data analysis (EDA)
- Feature engineering
- Machine learning prediction tasks

A sample version of the dataset is included in this repository for demonstration
and reproducibility purposes.

The dataset captures important aspects of football gameplay such as passing,
possession, shots, fouls, discipline statistics, and defensive actions,
providing a comprehensive view of match dynamics.


Match Structure:
Each row corresponds to one football match and includes:
- General match information (season, date, teams)
- Home team statistics
- Away team statistics
- Final match outcome


Columns Included:
The dataset contains both numerical and categorical columns such as:
- season
- date
- home_team
- away_team
- goal_home_ft
- goal_away_ft
- shots
- shots on target
- possession
- passes
- fouls
- yellow cards
- red cards
- corners
- offsides
- tackles
- clearances


Key Features:
The dataset includes football-related metrics such as:
- Passing and possession statistics
- Offensive performance metrics
- Defensive actions
- Discipline indicators
- Match outcome information
- Goal statistics


Outcome Representation:
Match results are represented using:
- goal_home_ft : goals scored by the home team
- goal_away_ft : goals scored by the away team
- sg_match_ft  : goal difference (home − away)
- result       : final match outcome
                 (Home Win, Draw, Away Win)


Class Distribution:
The dataset follows a realistic football outcome distribution:
- Home Wins : majority of matches
- Away Wins : slightly fewer than home wins
- Draws     : least frequent outcome


Purpose of the Dataset:
This dataset supports a wide range of analytical and predictive tasks, including:
- SQL analytics
- Team performance analysis
- Matchup analysis
- Trend exploration
- Data visualization
- Feature engineering
- Match outcome prediction
- Over/Under goals prediction

The dataset serves as the foundation for the complete SQL, Python,
and Machine Learning pipeline developed in this repository.
